May the World,...see this. GODBless ya Johnny,...we All make mistakes,...nobody is perfect,...and Amber was your worst.

column2: Up until ATurd wrote and published her defamatory co-op to the public, JD has worked very single year since his very first movie.  He hasn’t worked a day since then.  She intentionally and maliciously ruined the character, reputation, and CAREER of a beloved and innocent man.  She’s an ADMITTED and DOCUMENTED ABUSER and should be in jail for assault and perjury.  He has fought and won his case, which is fantastic!!! and most will welcome him back with open arms.  However, bc he had to share his most private, ugliest and darkest moments with the world, he may never be seen the same again by many.  The world is a highly judgemental place. The public shame and humiliation AH has put him through is unimaginable…I hope she suffers 100,000,000x greater for what she has done to his life.  98% of people around the world agree - and she is the most hated woman in the world right now for a very good reason.  She’s a narcissistic, vile, disgusting, EVIL, con-artist fraud and master manipulator who MUST BE HELD ACCOUNTABLE FOR ALL HER CRIMES  - AND GAZILLION PERJURY LIES.  He’s a humble, kind, generous, loving man who never deserved an ounce of this.  My heart is truly broken for all those out there who wind up in JD’s shoes.  JD will undoubtedly work again, he’s box office gold right now, and always has been - but sadly, his reputation will always be a bit tarnished out there in the world…thanks to Amber Turd.  I hope she is blackballed for life from movies magazines and campaigns!!!

column2:
Johnny never deserved what occurred to him. He was put through so much bc of his ex wife Amber Heard and to add insult to LITERAL injury,  his career was blacklisted! Guilty before knowing the truth. This cancel culture needs to chill. Film studios need to take a step back and see who Johnny was whilst working with him. What others say about him and investigate, not toss someone to the curb by 1 person. It's so sad to see what he's endured and still Johnny gave his heart and soul on screen and in public and even in his private life, that to me means he's a genuine soul, a pure loving soul. Johnny is whom he says he is, and to me he's "True Gentleman." 
Side note.. Johnny wants something...He wants to be knighted. Make it happen he is more than deserving. He needs apologies as well.

column2:
I will not support a self-confessed, yet unrepentant, abuser of at least two of her domestic partners. 
I’m signing because I’ve heard the tapes Ms Heard made in which she admits repeatedly hitting Mr. Depp, states she can’t promise not to again, clearly gaslights Mr. Depp, and engages in further violent & disgusting behaviors typical of some Cluster B personality disordered people- particularly Malignant Narcissism. In the tapes Mr. Depp can be heard endeavoring to navigate kindly in an impossible situation with someone behaving like a toxic malignant narcissist- classic conversation between abuser (Heard) & victim (Depp). Heard also has a verifiable legal history as a domestic abuser, which points to repetition compulsion.
Mr. Depp has surely lost too much already, let’s not continue to victimize and penalize him for the simple “crime” of falling for a girlmonster. Conversely let’s not reward Ms. Heard for her terrible behavior.
Both parties need help- Ms. Heard needs a 12 step & vitamin therapy for alcoholism, and Cognitive Behavioural Therapy; and Mr Depp needs trauma counseling, research on & therapy to heal his possible attachment disorder, & heal with holistic health therapies, along with Adeno B12 and top notch Genomic B-complex therapy. Both parties need to heal. And the world at large should Not be further abused by having to view films by, or be further gaslighted by, Heard.

column2:
i find it ridiculous that he has been removed from his roles from iconic movies that wouldn't be watchable without him, he has given others a voice to listen to when they had nothing else, he has brought light and a beacon of hope to so many.
he is one of the few actors to have such a meaningful and impressive carer and to have it destroyed by this lying torturous excuse of a human shows how much he has had to go through just to look after his life and his children's. hopefully they will go to court and have a fair judge who pays attention to all of the evidence and does not falsely accuse someone of abusing another when it is obviously in fact the other way around and Mr Depp is the victim.
there is no way that many film series can successfully continue without the addition of Mr Depp so i am signing this in hope that people will stop wasting oxygen on false accusations and figure out what is actually the truth. 
also i like many fans will not continue watching the series if Mr Depp is not in them.

thankyou if you read. sorry if i took up your time with my rant.

column2:
Ms Heard claimed to have donated millions of her divorce settlement to two charities. Subsequent court proceedings indicate that years later they have not received any donations from her. Charities rely on people making good on their pledge so that they can help those that are less fortunate. She pledged $3.5m to each charity, a total of $7m.

- I will no longer support any charity or cause Ms Heard is an ambassador of. (Apologies to the charities but you will need to find more appropriate advocates or ambassadors).

- I will no longer buy or support any product Ms Heard is promoting, paid or otherwise. Including employment in any capacity she has in any aspect within the media, particularly the movie industry.

column2: Johnny Depp is an amazing actor and he deserves to get his job back. It's unfair what happened to him. Johnny Depp didn't do anything to deserve this. There are many people who are punished for something they didn't do, but this is too far. Johnny Depp lost not only his job, but his life. Not only that, but some people are trying to cover up what happened by saying Johnny just retired. Johnny Depp needs his job back. He's one of the best actors out there, and he needs to share his talent with the world, but he can't do it alone. We need to help Johnny Depp.
